<section id="about" class="bg-light">
  <div class="grid-x">
    <div class="cell small-12">
      <h5>21 years running!</h5>
      <p>We've been doing this for a while now! Once again, this year's Summer Gathering will be filled with lectures about news and new toys, plenty of show-and-tell, food, and antennas.</p>
      <p>As usual, the event will be held at <a href="https://valleycamp.org">Valley Camp</a>. For reservations please contact <a href="mailto:info@valleycamp.org">info@valleycamp.org</a>.</p>
      <p>For questions, please contact <a href="mailto:summergathering@wa7vc.org">summergathering@wa7vc.org</a>.</p>
      <p>To stay up to date on the latest news, <a href="https://tinyletter.com/nwaprssg" target="_blank">sign up for the newsletter <i class="fas fa-external-link-alt"></i></a>. (We promise, we don't send too many emails!)</p>

      <h5>Friends, food, and RF. </h5>
      <p>Breakfast on Saturday and Sunday will be provided, and Coffee will be available! Donations to help cover this cost gratefully accepted. Lunch on Saturday will also be provided, stay tuned for the menu! Dinner on Saturday will likely be "bring your won" but we'll have a hot BBQ available!</p>
      <p>Got Ham Radio related equipment to sell, trade or offer for free? Bring it along and make it available from your tailgate, trunk, side door, backpack, or pocket during the event. (Best times will be meal breaks and evenings)</p>
      <p>
        Event Talk-In Frequencies will be the WA7VC local frequencies:
        <ul>
          <li>70cm Simplex: 446.525 (no tone). IRLP Node 7808, Echolink Node 98045</li>
          <li>DSTAR: WA7VC B on 440.01250Mhz + 5.000Mhz</li>
          <li>DMR: We will be monitoring Washington 2. A demonstration Motorola DMR repeater will be onsite. (<a href="http://trbo.org/pnw/demonstration.html" target="_blank">Demonstration Project Information <i class="fas fa-external-link-alt"></i></a>)</li>
        </ul>
      </p>
  </div>
</section>


